86C 101st Legislative Session 86
2026 South Dakota Legislature
Senate Bill 86
AMENDM ENT 86C
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Peterson (Sue)
1 An Act to authorize purchasing agency verification and monitoring of workers'
2 compensation insurance coverage obtained require that certain contracts
3 include a provision for the purchasing agency to verify and monitor workers'
4 compensation insurance carried by public improvement contractors.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
6 Section 1. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 5-18B:
7 Any contract for a public improvement between a contractor and a purchasing
8 agency, as those terms are defined in § 5-18A-1, must contain a provision authorizing the
9 purchasing agency to:
10 (1) Verify that the contractor has obtained workers' compensation insurance, as
11 provided in title 62, prior to the commencement of any contracted service and
12 whether, under the worker's compensation insurance policy, the contractor's
13 estimated payroll is zero; and
14 (2) Monitor the status of the contractor's workers' compensation insurance coverage
15 during the pendency of the contract by requesting that the contractor provide:
16 (a) Documentation showing the contractor's payment of workers' compensation
17 insurance premiums;
18 (b) A list of all subcontractors involved with the public improvement;
19 (c) Payroll records of the contractor's employees and any subcontractor's
20 employees involved with the public improvement; and
21 (d) Any other information deemed necessary by the purchasing agency to
22 prevent the occurrence of workers' compensation fraud in connection with
23 the public improvement.
24 Section 2. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 5-18B:
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

86C 2 86
1 If a contractor or a subcontractor fails to comply with any provision of a contract
2 for public improvement, which is required by this chapter, the purchasing agency may
3 terminate the contract for cause, recover any damages arising from the noncompliance,
4 and replace the contractor or subcontractor.
